REM Networking
docker build -t canopy-api .
docker network create canopy-net

REM Run the API Container (includes volume mounting - data will be lost when the container stops unless you mount a volume)
REM Run the API container first (it must exist before the scraper tries to reach it)
docker run -d ^
  --name canopy-api ^
  --network canopy-net ^
  -p 8080:80 ^
  -e API_KEY=test747646s5d4fvasfd645654asgasga654a6g13a2fg465a4fg4a3 ^
  -v C:\data\results:/app/CanopyResults ^
  -v C:\data\logs:/app/logging ^
  canopy-api

REM Run the Scraper Container
docker build -t canopy-scraper .

docker run -it ^
  --name canopy-scraper ^
  --network canopy-net ^
  -e API_URL=http://canopy-api/results ^
  canopy-scraper

REM View running containers
docker ps

REM View logs
docker logs canopy-api

REM Stop a container
docker stop canopy-api

REM Remove a container
docker rm canopy-api

REM Inspect the network
docker network inspect canopy-net

The URL is **not arbitrary** — each part has a specific meaning:

## Breaking Down `http://canopy-api/results`

```
http://canopy-api/results
         ↑           ↑
   container name   endpoint defined
   = Docker DNS     in your Saturn router
```

### `canopy-api` — NOT freely chosen here
This must **exactly match** the `--name` you gave the API container:
```cmd
docker run --name canopy-api ...
```
Docker's internal DNS resolves container names automatically within the same network. If you named it `my-api` you'd write `http://my-api/results`.

### `/results` — must match your Saturn router
This must match an endpoint defined in your `apiRouter`:
```fsharp
let apiRouter =
    router
        {
            get "/"         (linksHandler pathCanopy)
            put "/"         (putHandler pathCanopy)
            get "/jsonLinks" (linksHandler pathJsonLinks)
            put "/jsonLinks" (putHandler pathJsonLinks)
            get "/logging"  (logEntriesHandler pathLogEntries)
            post "/logging" (postHandler pathLogEntries)
        }
```
So the valid URLs from the scraper container would be:
```
http://canopy-api/
http://canopy-api/jsonLinks
http://canopy-api/logging
```

---

## Rule of Thumb

| Part | Freely chosen?    | Must match |
|---   |             ---   |         ---|
| `http://`    | Fixed     |          — |
| `canopy-api` | No        | `--name` of the API container  |
| `/results`   | No        | Route defined in Saturn router |